	| It remains here for backward compatability only. |
	+--------------------------------------------------+


Calendar User Control Class v1.21 (Last updated on 09-Oct-97)
==============================================================

The Calendar user control can be painted on a form to provide 
the functionality of a month calendar. It is a subclass of the
standard BaseControl class.

As a default the Calendar control displays the current date,
which can be changed by clicking on the particular day within
the month/year displayed, or by using buttons next to the
month/year labels to increase/decrease month/year.


--------------------------------------------------------------
Attribute		Value		Description
--------------------------------------------------------------
date			any date	Get/set current calendar date

changeType		0			No change
				1			Day button clicked
				2			Month button clicked
				3			Year button clicked
				4			Date changed from the script


--------------------------------------------------------------
Events			Description
--------------------------------------------------------------				
click			This event is triggered when current Calendar
				date is changed. The current Calendar date can
				be changed by clicking on Day, Month, or Year
				buttons, or by changing the value of date 
				attribute from within the script.

mouseDown		This is triggered only when the mouse is over
				the month table subcontrol.

--------------------------------------------------------------
Constants					Value
--------------------------------------------------------------
ChangeType_None				0
ChangeType_Day				1
ChangeType_Month			2
ChangeType_Year				3
ChangeType_Script			4


Limitations
-----------
Changing the value of foreColor property in the Painter will not 
change the colors displayed in the Painter. The form must be run
for the actual colors to be displayed.

Although it is possible, in the Painter, to change the default 
values for the properties borderStyle, show3D, and transparent,  
those changes will not have any effect, neither in the Painter 
nor in the runtime.


Changes Since Version 1.0
-------------------------
New property dayNameLength has been added to control the length of
day of the week names in a calendar. The default value is 3.</text>
